olive oil
3 potato
1 sachet mixed sesame seeds
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 egg
1 packet teriyaki sauce
2 Butter Burger Buns
1 pear
1 sprig spring onion
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with mixed sesame seeds and season with salt.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help sprinkle over the sesame seeds and tossing the fries.

• While the fries are baking, combine beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, sweet soy seasoning and the egg in a large bowl.
• Using damp hands, shape the beef mixture into 2cm-thick patties (1 per person).
• When the fries have 10 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook beef patties until just cooked through, 5-6 minutes on each side. Remove pan from heat, then add teriyaki sauce and turn to coat.

TIP: Cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded.
Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the ingredients and shaping the mixture into patties!

• Meanwhile, halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.
• Thinly slice pear and spring onion.
• In a medium bowl, add shredded cabbage mix, pear, spring onion and mayonnaise. Toss to combine.

• Top burger buns with a teriyaki-glazed beef patty and some creamy slaw.
• Serve with sesame fries and any remaining slaw. Enjoy!